width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></noscript></a></figure><p>Maintain in-flight comfort and cleanliness by wearing breathable fabrics—materials like cotton, silk, or linen. Fabrics that don’t allow air to circulate will hold in sweat, likely making you feel dirtier faster and probably necessitating a good spin in the washing machine upon landing. Natural fabrics are great, but moisture-wicking manmade fabrics are suitable options as well: <a href="https://www.rei.com/product/119998/rei-co-op-streelowe-leggings-womens" target="_blank" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener">Streelowe Leggings from REI Co-op</a> are a polyester/spandex blend that’s incredibly quick-drying.</p>




