<p>Don’t throw fashion out the window. When it comes to dressing for a flight, a lot of advice focuses on function. But dressing with a bit of style—while keeping conscious of comfort of course—could help you get a free upgrade. An anonymous source once <a href="https://goop.com/travel/experiences/fly-better-tricks-for-better-plane-trips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">told Goop</a>: “On a Virgin flight back to Heathrow, I spotted one of the staff’s monitors that read, ‘Look for well-dressed people to upgrade.’” This won’t happen every time, but if you are <a href="https://www.smartertravel.com/first-class-free-get-airline-upgrade/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">hoping to get upgraded</a>, it helps to look smart. <a href="https://www.grayson.com/products/the-hero-cool-cotton-plaids" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Button-downs by Grayson</a> are flowy but still look good once you disembark. For men, a classic, logo-free tee like <a href="https://www.everlane.com/products/mens-premium-weight-crew-crocodile" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">this one</a> from Everlane is comfortable without being restrictive and will let you blend in anywhere.</p>





